        "behavior": "; 74174 — hex D-type flip-flop with a common asynchronous master reset.\n; Derived from the function table (datasheet Table 3): while /MR is LOW all\n; six outputs are forced LOW asynchronously; otherwise each output Qn loads\n; the value of Dn at the LOW-to-HIGH transition of CP.\n;\n; SEQUENTIAL-PART CLOCK CONVENTION (74574.yaml): GALasm's .R registered\n; outputs are clocked by the GAL22V10's dedicated pin-1 clock\n; (galasmManual.txt section 3.4). That pin-1 clock role is played by the\n; part's named clock pin — here CP, rising-edge triggered. CP therefore does\n; NOT appear as a term in any equation below; the .R suffix implies it.\n;\n; The asynchronous master reset uses GALasm's global AR (galasmManual.txt\n; section 3.6): while its term is true every register is held at 0,\n; independent of the clock. Pin /MR is active LOW, so AR = /MR.\n;\n; Equations are physical-level GALasm: '/' is the complement operator and\n; signal names are this file's pin names with any active-low '/' prefix\n; dropped (pin /MR is GAL signal MR, so '/MR' means \"pin /MR is LOW\").\nAR   = /MR\nQ0.R = D0\nQ1.R = D1\nQ2.R = D2\nQ3.R = D3\nQ4.R = D4\nQ5.R = D5\n",
        "clock": "CP",
        "description": "Hex D flip-flop with common async reset, positive edge-trigger",
        "datasheet": {
          "vendor": "Nexperia",
          "title": "74HC174; 74HCT174 Hex D-type flip-flop with reset; positive-edge trigger",
          "rev": "Rev. 7, 14 March 2024",
          "url": "https://assets.nexperia.com/documents/data-sheet/74HC_HCT174.pdf"
        }
      },
